1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:03,044
♪ <i>Oh, Mr. Tailor…</i> ♪

2
00:00:04,129 --> 00:00:07,882
["Tailor" playing]

3
00:00:09,050 --> 00:00:10,760
♪ <i>Oh, Mr. Tailor</i> ♪

4
00:00:10,844 --> 00:00:12,929
♪ <i>Holding the scissors</i> ♪

5
00:00:13,012 --> 00:00:15,015
♪ <i>One cut, and it's settled</i> ♪

6
00:00:15,098 --> 00:00:16,725
♪ <i>In the world's mess</i> ♪

7
00:00:16,808 --> 00:00:18,560
[Tonet] <i>My older brother is…</i>

8
00:00:18,643 --> 00:00:19,602
<i>Emerson.</i>

9
00:00:19,686 --> 00:00:21,563
[Cita] <i>Huh? My goodness!</i>

10
00:00:21,646 --> 00:00:22,772
You know each other?

11
00:00:22,856 --> 00:00:25,650
Big Brother, I'm Netchai! Your sister!

12
00:00:25,734 --> 00:00:27,819
[Emerson] <i>You're the sister I loved most.</i>

13
00:00:27,902 --> 00:00:30,155
<i>Then you left me. And now what?</i>

14
00:00:30,238 --> 00:00:31,656
[Emerson] <i>I don't want</i>
<i>to see your face here!</i>

15
00:00:31,740 --> 00:00:33,575
[Atoy] <i>Take it easy! Show her some mercy.</i>

16
00:00:33,658 --> 00:00:35,994
[Emerson] <i>You always want to be</i>
<i>the main character among us!</i>

17
00:00:36,077 --> 00:00:37,370
- <i>You're the most handsome!</i>
- [bone cracks]

18
00:00:37,454 --> 00:00:38,455
<i>You're the best!</i>

19
00:00:38,538 --> 00:00:39,789
- [people clamoring]
- [Emerson grunts]

20
00:00:39,873 --> 00:00:41,458
[man] <i>No one wants to fight you here!</i>

21
00:00:41,541 --> 00:00:45,086
[Atoy] MatchTayo. This is the app
used by another girl

22
00:00:45,170 --> 00:00:46,421
who's been missing for a month now.

23
00:00:46,504 --> 00:00:48,256
[Peping] I don't understand.

24
00:00:48,339 --> 00:00:50,008
But go ahead, son! Six seven.

25
00:00:50,091 --> 00:00:52,802
[Atoy] <i>Raki. Raki Roman.</i>

26
00:00:52,886 --> 00:00:54,596
I have a table there. Come on.
Hey, I'm trying to be nice here.

27
00:00:54,679 --> 00:00:55,764
Why are you so arrogant?

28
00:00:55,847 --> 00:00:57,766
I just want to drink alone!

29
00:00:57,849 --> 00:00:59,100
[barman] <i>Raki, leave Tonet alone.</i>

30
00:00:59,184 --> 00:01:01,561
Even if he hides in the eye of a needle,

31
00:01:02,228 --> 00:01:03,772
I'll find him.

32
00:01:03,855 --> 00:01:05,231
PREVIOUSLY

33
00:01:07,067 --> 00:01:09,110
[opening song continues]

34
00:01:09,986 --> 00:01:11,863
[upbeat bar music playing]

35
00:01:11,946 --> 00:01:13,364
Your handler said

36
00:01:13,907 --> 00:01:15,200
you still have gigs tomorrow.

37
00:01:15,825 --> 00:01:17,035
You've had too much to drink.

38
00:01:17,702 --> 00:01:20,330
You're Tonet? Right.

39
00:01:21,372 --> 00:01:22,999
[in English] See you again soon.

40
00:01:23,833 --> 00:01:24,667
Okay, bro.

41
00:01:25,835 --> 00:01:28,129
[bustling chattering]

42
00:01:30,757 --> 00:01:33,051
Mmm. Please excuse Raki.

43
00:01:35,595 --> 00:01:36,596
Thanks.

44
00:01:37,472 --> 00:01:39,641
How did you know my name?

45
00:01:40,475 --> 00:01:42,435
Didn't you hang out here
with your friends?

46
00:01:42,936 --> 00:01:44,562
I heard her say your name.

47
00:01:45,063 --> 00:01:47,524
It's easy to remember.

48
00:01:47,607 --> 00:01:48,900
I'm Enzo.

49
00:01:49,484 --> 00:01:50,693
Tonet.

50
00:01:50,777 --> 00:01:56,366
Since you're here, give me
the strongest alcoholic drink.

51
00:01:56,449 --> 00:01:57,867
Give me 20 of those.

52
00:01:57,951 --> 00:01:59,661
No, just kidding. Just three.

53
00:01:59,744 --> 00:02:01,037
I thought you don't drink?

54
00:02:01,121 --> 00:02:02,539
Only if there's a reason.

55
00:02:02,622 --> 00:02:04,332
Looks like you have many reasons.

56
00:02:04,415 --> 00:02:05,792
- All right.
- You said it.

57
00:02:05,875 --> 00:02:07,252
[Tonet inhales]

58
00:02:08,503 --> 00:02:10,171
- Three?
- [Tonet] That's it!

59
00:02:10,755 --> 00:02:13,258
- I'll move over there.
- [Enzo] Okay, I'll serve it there.

60
00:02:20,306 --> 00:02:21,474
[disgusted groan]

61
00:02:24,602 --> 00:02:27,230
[bustling chattering]

62
00:02:27,313 --> 00:02:29,440
Is this really what I ordered earlier?

63
00:02:29,524 --> 00:02:30,692
[Enzo] Oh, no.

64
00:02:30,775 --> 00:02:31,734
[Enzo sighs]

65
00:02:32,235 --> 00:02:34,779
That's iced water. Easy.

66
00:02:35,280 --> 00:02:36,698
Drink water in between.

67
00:02:36,781 --> 00:02:39,075
Or else, you'll have
a bad hangover tomorrow.

68
00:02:39,159 --> 00:02:42,203
And I'm sure you'll still have problems.

69
00:02:44,539 --> 00:02:46,374
Better if you let it out.

70
00:02:47,208 --> 00:02:50,086
[in English] No judgment zone.
Safe space here.

71
00:02:50,920 --> 00:02:52,130
[in English] Boy problems?

72
00:02:52,213 --> 00:02:53,840
[in English] Family issues?

73
00:02:54,841 --> 00:02:55,925
[in English] Both.

74
00:02:56,009 --> 00:02:58,344
A man in the family.

75
00:02:59,387 --> 00:03:00,805
[in English] I'm all ears.

76
00:03:00,889 --> 00:03:04,058
[bustling chattering]

77
00:03:04,142 --> 00:03:07,437
[pensive music playing]

78
00:03:26,122 --> 00:03:27,290
[music swells]

79
00:03:28,416 --> 00:03:29,959
[music fades]

80
00:03:37,884 --> 00:03:40,511
[rock music playing]

81
00:04:01,115 --> 00:04:02,492
Hello! Miss…

82
00:04:03,368 --> 00:04:04,535
Miss!

83
00:04:04,619 --> 00:04:06,287
Yes? Do you have an appointment?

84
00:04:06,788 --> 00:04:10,375
No. I'm looking for someone. Raki Roman.

85
00:04:10,875 --> 00:04:12,752
There's no artist here named Roman.

86
00:04:13,336 --> 00:04:14,170
Not Roman!

87
00:04:14,254 --> 00:04:16,839
Raki! I'm looking for Raki Roman.

88
00:04:18,466 --> 00:04:19,676
Hello!

89
00:04:20,510 --> 00:04:21,344
Miss?

90
00:04:28,017 --> 00:04:29,060
[music stops]

91
00:04:29,143 --> 00:04:32,689
[tense music playing]

92
00:04:37,485 --> 00:04:38,653
[in English] Sorry, sorry.

93
00:04:39,153 --> 00:04:40,822
I'm just looking for someone.

94
00:04:41,948 --> 00:04:43,700
His name's Raki Roman.

95
00:04:43,783 --> 00:04:45,910
[tense music playing]

96
00:04:46,995 --> 00:04:47,829
[man] Are you a cop?

97
00:04:50,415 --> 00:04:51,249
No.

98
00:04:53,084 --> 00:04:54,210
I just need to talk to him.

99
00:04:55,295 --> 00:04:57,547
He's busy. Just leave.

100
00:05:01,551 --> 00:05:05,013
- [music player clicks]
- [rock music playing]

101
00:05:16,441 --> 00:05:19,110
[sauve music playing]

102
00:05:42,383 --> 00:05:43,885
[music fades]

103
00:05:43,968 --> 00:05:46,137
[bustling chattering]

104
00:05:46,220 --> 00:05:50,391
Big Brother Emerson
is my only real family here, and…

105
00:05:51,726 --> 00:05:53,728
this happened to us.

106
00:05:53,811 --> 00:05:54,979
[Enzo] Well, you should…

107
00:05:55,063 --> 00:05:58,232
[in English] Just give him space
and enough time to think.

108
00:05:59,150 --> 00:06:00,902
It's not easy for him either.

109
00:06:01,569 --> 00:06:06,282
You know, gradually remind him
of your shared moments.

110
00:06:08,743 --> 00:06:11,662
Tell him things you used to do together.

111
00:06:12,330 --> 00:06:14,207
It'll make him nostalgic.

112
00:06:14,832 --> 00:06:17,627
Then he'll remember your bond.

113
00:06:18,669 --> 00:06:22,715
You can rebuild connections
without being pushy.

114
00:06:23,591 --> 00:06:26,552
Slowly, once you make him smile…

115
00:06:27,512 --> 00:06:29,347
That's the start of forgiveness.

116
00:06:32,683 --> 00:06:36,062
And if you're still troubled after that,

117
00:06:36,145 --> 00:06:38,022
and want to hype yourself the next day…

118
00:06:39,357 --> 00:06:41,984
I'll send you my recommended playlist.

119
00:06:43,402 --> 00:06:45,905
Listen to it. Munting Sigaw.

120
00:06:46,489 --> 00:06:48,241
That's Raki's band.

121
00:06:48,324 --> 00:06:49,617
[Tonet] Eeh.

122
00:06:51,202 --> 00:06:52,161
What's this?

123
00:06:54,455 --> 00:06:58,126
[heavy rock music playing]

124
00:07:00,336 --> 00:07:01,629
[Tonet giggles]

125
00:07:02,630 --> 00:07:04,298
I'm not really into rock.

126
00:07:04,382 --> 00:07:07,385
But I appreciate it. Thank you.

127
00:07:07,468 --> 00:07:08,719
Of course.

128
00:07:11,764 --> 00:07:14,725
So, are you okay here now?

129
00:07:16,436 --> 00:07:18,438
- I'm okay now.
- [Enzo] I'll get back to work.

130
00:07:19,230 --> 00:07:21,524
- [in English] Thank you.
- [in English] Got you.

131
00:07:21,607 --> 00:07:22,692
Water!

132
00:07:22,775 --> 00:07:23,860
[bustling chattering]

133
00:07:23,943 --> 00:07:28,698
[sentimental music playing]

134
00:07:28,781 --> 00:07:30,825
[rock music playing]

135
00:07:30,908 --> 00:07:31,993
[man grunts]

136
00:07:33,536 --> 00:07:34,787
[grunting and groaning]

137
00:07:35,705 --> 00:07:38,082
[grunting and groaning]

138
00:07:38,166 --> 00:07:40,293
[grunting and groaning]

139
00:07:48,009 --> 00:07:48,968
[bone cracks]

140
00:07:56,225 --> 00:07:57,602
Where are you going?!

141
00:07:57,685 --> 00:07:58,519
[man groans]

142
00:08:12,366 --> 00:08:15,912
[music continues playing]

143
00:08:15,995 --> 00:08:17,497
[grunting]

144
00:08:18,206 --> 00:08:19,040
[Raki groans]

145
00:08:24,754 --> 00:08:25,922
I'm sorry.

146
00:08:26,005 --> 00:08:27,965
- [sinister music playing]
- You kept running away earlier.

147
00:08:28,049 --> 00:08:29,884
I just wanted to tell you something.

148
00:08:29,967 --> 00:08:33,054
And your friends…

149
00:08:33,137 --> 00:08:36,057
I just calmed them down a bit.

150
00:08:36,140 --> 00:08:37,308
Where are you going?

151
00:08:37,391 --> 00:08:39,060
What do you want from me?!

152
00:08:39,143 --> 00:08:40,978
I just want to ask you.

153
00:08:41,062 --> 00:08:43,523
- Huh? [grunts]
- [coughs]

154
00:08:43,606 --> 00:08:45,358
[grunts, panting]

155
00:08:45,983 --> 00:08:47,276
[Atoy] Do you know who that is?

156
00:08:47,360 --> 00:08:49,237
- [Raki] I don't know!
- [Atoy] You don't know?

157
00:08:49,320 --> 00:08:50,613
I don't know who that is!

158
00:08:50,696 --> 00:08:54,617
Maybe you want me to calm you down too?!
Who is that?

159
00:08:54,700 --> 00:08:56,285
[Raki grunts]

160
00:08:56,369 --> 00:08:58,162
That's Queenie. I dated her before!

161
00:08:58,246 --> 00:08:59,330
How many days?

162
00:09:00,248 --> 00:09:01,374
How many days?!

163
00:09:01,457 --> 00:09:02,667
Oh, I don't… I don't know!

164
00:09:02,750 --> 00:09:04,585
I was with her, but I left right away!

165
00:09:04,669 --> 00:09:06,462
They say she hasn't gone home for days.

166
00:09:07,046 --> 00:09:08,506
What do you know about this, huh?

167
00:09:08,589 --> 00:09:10,383
[Raki grunts and coughs]

168
00:09:10,466 --> 00:09:12,843
This one, Mandy.

169
00:09:13,344 --> 00:09:14,387
Do you know Mandy?

170
00:09:15,096 --> 00:09:16,055
Huh?

171
00:09:16,138 --> 00:09:18,307
She hasn't gone home for a month.

172
00:09:18,391 --> 00:09:19,642
Do you have anything to do with this?

173
00:09:19,725 --> 00:09:20,726
Did you date her too?!

174
00:09:20,810 --> 00:09:21,978
[Raki coughs]

175
00:09:22,061 --> 00:09:23,980
- [Atoy] What? Huh?!
- [Raki panting]

176
00:09:24,063 --> 00:09:25,147
I don't know anything!

177
00:09:25,231 --> 00:09:28,025
[grunts and groans]

178
00:09:29,026 --> 00:09:32,446
[action music playing]

179
00:09:32,530 --> 00:09:34,657
[grunting and groaning]

180
00:09:42,748 --> 00:09:44,917
[tense music playing]

181
00:10:10,693 --> 00:10:11,736
[Ibyang] Oh, Master?

182
00:10:13,988 --> 00:10:17,366
Are you hungry or just in a bad mood?

183
00:10:17,450 --> 00:10:18,743
Both.

184
00:10:18,826 --> 00:10:20,620
The suspect was able to escape.

185
00:10:21,454 --> 00:10:24,582
Then eat first, so you'll feel happy.

186
00:10:24,665 --> 00:10:27,043
I will eat indeed. Did you read earlier?

187
00:10:28,502 --> 00:10:29,378
[Ibyang] Yes!

188
00:10:29,462 --> 00:10:32,757
The book you gave me earlier?

189
00:10:32,840 --> 00:10:35,176
- Oh?
- [Ibyang] There's another story there.

190
00:10:35,259 --> 00:10:36,177
What story?

191
00:10:40,473 --> 00:10:41,766
[playful music playing]

192
00:10:41,849 --> 00:10:45,603
Mmm! [mumbling]

193
00:10:51,442 --> 00:10:52,276
Huh?

194
00:10:52,360 --> 00:10:54,153
- [mumbling]
- [Atoy chuckles]

195
00:10:54,236 --> 00:10:56,155
- I wish I understood.
- [mumbling]

196
00:10:56,238 --> 00:10:57,239
What did you say?

197
00:10:57,323 --> 00:11:02,203
[mumbling]

198
00:11:02,286 --> 00:11:03,663
I can't hear… What did you say?

199
00:11:03,746 --> 00:11:05,665
[Ibyang mumbling]

200
00:11:05,748 --> 00:11:07,500
[Atoy] Oh, then?

201
00:11:07,583 --> 00:11:10,378
[mumbling]

202
00:11:11,003 --> 00:11:14,882
[playful music continues]

203
00:11:17,343 --> 00:11:18,427
[Atoy] Oh, then?

204
00:11:18,928 --> 00:11:20,471
Hmm…

205
00:11:21,722 --> 00:11:22,807
Hmm?

206
00:11:23,808 --> 00:11:28,104
[in English] And they lived
happily ever after!

207
00:11:28,187 --> 00:11:29,021
[Atoy] Ah!

208
00:11:29,105 --> 00:11:32,066
- [in English] Lived happily ever after.
- [in English] The end.

209
00:11:32,149 --> 00:11:34,360
That's a beautiful story.

210
00:11:35,861 --> 00:11:37,738
We don't have utensils.

211
00:11:41,200 --> 00:11:42,493
[utensils clatter]

212
00:11:43,327 --> 00:11:45,621
[somber music playing]

213
00:11:45,704 --> 00:11:47,706
Oh! Uh…

214
00:11:48,290 --> 00:11:49,375
Here.

215
00:11:50,418 --> 00:11:52,420
Ibyang, read this.

216
00:11:52,503 --> 00:11:54,672
- Uh…
- Mmm, this.

217
00:11:55,965 --> 00:11:57,258
Don't you want some food?

218
00:11:57,341 --> 00:11:59,135
There's adobo in the fridge.

219
00:11:59,218 --> 00:12:00,886
- I'll just heat it up instead of ordering.
- No, no, no, no.

220
00:12:00,970 --> 00:12:02,513
I don't want adobo.

221
00:12:03,013 --> 00:12:04,723
- Oh…
- This, this. I want you to read this.

222
00:12:04,807 --> 00:12:06,350
Here. Start here.

223
00:12:07,309 --> 00:12:08,853
Go on. Read it.

224
00:12:09,478 --> 00:12:10,521
From here.

225
00:12:16,569 --> 00:12:18,404
[yawns]

226
00:12:18,487 --> 00:12:21,532
You know, I'm sleepy.

227
00:12:21,615 --> 00:12:24,535
Can I just do it tomorrow? I'll sleep now.

228
00:12:24,618 --> 00:12:25,995
Oop, oop, oop, oop, wait.

229
00:12:26,078 --> 00:12:29,331
Don't, don't, don't you run away from me.

230
00:12:29,415 --> 00:12:30,916
I said, read it.

231
00:12:32,042 --> 00:12:33,335
Read it.

232
00:12:34,170 --> 00:12:35,212
I'm hungry.

233
00:12:35,296 --> 00:12:36,839
I want to know. What's this?

234
00:12:36,922 --> 00:12:38,674
Here. From here.

235
00:12:38,757 --> 00:12:39,758
Go on.

236
00:12:42,553 --> 00:12:43,471
Read it.

237
00:12:44,138 --> 00:12:45,473
[utensils clatter, then thud]

238
00:12:46,140 --> 00:12:49,059
Ibyang, read it.

239
00:12:49,143 --> 00:12:51,770
[somber music playing]

240
00:12:51,854 --> 00:12:52,897
Ibyang!

241
00:12:58,110 --> 00:12:59,361
Do you know… Just this part.

242
00:12:59,445 --> 00:13:00,863
Here. Oh, oh.

243
00:13:04,658 --> 00:13:07,953
[sobbing]

244
00:13:08,037 --> 00:13:10,748
Sorry, Master.

245
00:13:11,373 --> 00:13:12,458
[sobbing]

246
00:13:12,541 --> 00:13:15,878
Don't be mad at me.

247
00:13:16,420 --> 00:13:17,254
[sobs]

248
00:13:17,338 --> 00:13:19,548
I just can't do it.

249
00:13:20,966 --> 00:13:24,136
I don't know how to read.

250
00:13:24,220 --> 00:13:26,138
[sobbing]

251
00:13:26,222 --> 00:13:29,558
Sorry if I lied.

252
00:13:31,018 --> 00:13:34,230
Sorry if I'm stupid!

253
00:13:34,313 --> 00:13:37,775
[sobbing]

254
00:13:43,197 --> 00:13:44,281
Ibyang…

255
00:13:45,824 --> 00:13:47,368
Hey, hey… Uh…

256
00:13:50,621 --> 00:13:53,374
Ibyang, don't say that.

257
00:13:53,457 --> 00:13:54,458
Come on.

258
00:13:54,542 --> 00:13:58,087
Ibyang, don't say that about yourself.

259
00:13:58,170 --> 00:13:59,296
Okay?

260
00:14:00,047 --> 00:14:02,174
You… You're not stupid, okay?

261
00:14:02,258 --> 00:14:03,175
You're not stupid.

262
00:14:03,801 --> 00:14:05,678
Never ever say that about yourself, okay?

263
00:14:05,761 --> 00:14:07,346
Psst, hey. This child…

264
00:14:07,429 --> 00:14:08,264
Come here.

265
00:14:08,347 --> 00:14:12,184
[somber music playing]

266
00:14:26,115 --> 00:14:27,283
[Atoy groans]

267
00:14:29,243 --> 00:14:32,079
Never ever say that about yourself, okay?

268
00:14:32,162 --> 00:14:33,873
You're not stupid.

269
00:14:34,748 --> 00:14:37,084
- [sniffles]
- Okay? Oh, sorry, sorry. I didn't know…

270
00:14:37,167 --> 00:14:39,211
I didn't know you couldn't read.

271
00:14:39,295 --> 00:14:42,381
[sobs] That was my secret.

272
00:14:42,464 --> 00:14:45,342
Even Sister Ame doesn't know.

273
00:14:46,051 --> 00:14:46,886
[in English] Secret?

274
00:14:48,304 --> 00:14:50,139
Why do you have a secret?

275
00:14:50,222 --> 00:14:51,932
[gentle music playing]

276
00:14:52,016 --> 00:14:53,183
Son of a--

277
00:14:54,184 --> 00:14:55,686
With your deviousness?

278
00:14:56,437 --> 00:14:58,439
You were able to keep that secret
because you're so cunning.

279
00:14:58,522 --> 00:15:01,650
No one would ever guess you can't read.

280
00:15:01,734 --> 00:15:03,527
[sniffles]

281
00:15:04,111 --> 00:15:05,821
No one taught you?

282
00:15:05,905 --> 00:15:08,866
I grew up in an orphanage.

283
00:15:08,949 --> 00:15:13,454
Volunteers read to us,

284
00:15:13,537 --> 00:15:16,165
taught us songs…

285
00:15:17,207 --> 00:15:18,876
and drawing.

286
00:15:18,959 --> 00:15:20,628
But that's all.

287
00:15:21,879 --> 00:15:25,507
Imagine, with all your shenanigans,
you still can't read?

288
00:15:26,300 --> 00:15:27,343
[chuckles]

289
00:15:28,260 --> 00:15:29,511
Sorry.

290
00:15:30,512 --> 00:15:34,808
But I'm good at acting.

291
00:15:34,892 --> 00:15:38,103
And I understand things quickly.

292
00:15:38,187 --> 00:15:40,356
Plus, I'm cute.

293
00:15:40,439 --> 00:15:44,068
Ahh. Yes, you are cute.

294
00:15:45,069 --> 00:15:47,196
But Ibyang, remember this.

295
00:15:47,279 --> 00:15:49,740
You'll struggle to survive in this world

296
00:15:49,823 --> 00:15:52,952
if all you do is act cute and pretend.

297
00:15:53,661 --> 00:15:58,082
It's important to learn to read and write.

298
00:15:58,582 --> 00:15:59,792
Hmm?

299
00:16:02,503 --> 00:16:04,463
Eh, um, uh…

300
00:16:05,130 --> 00:16:06,590
- Master…
- Mmm?

301
00:16:07,174 --> 00:16:09,635
Will you order pizza?

302
00:16:09,718 --> 00:16:11,220
- Oh, whoo! You want to order?
- Because…

303
00:16:11,303 --> 00:16:12,304
What do you want to order?

304
00:16:12,388 --> 00:16:13,847
This. This is what I want.

305
00:16:13,931 --> 00:16:15,015
- This is what you want?
- Yes, this is what I want.

306
00:16:15,099 --> 00:16:16,225
Me too, I want this.

307
00:16:16,308 --> 00:16:17,184
Oh.

308
00:16:17,267 --> 00:16:19,103
[in English] Maybe I should talk
to her brother?

309
00:16:19,728 --> 00:16:21,480
[in English] No! You do not do that!

310
00:16:21,563 --> 00:16:24,191
[in English] You do not solve
her family problems for her.

311
00:16:24,274 --> 00:16:25,651
That's meddling!

312
00:16:26,610 --> 00:16:28,862
[in English] Dude, I just feel so bad
for the way that Emerson guy

313
00:16:28,946 --> 00:16:30,698
was treating Tonet.

314
00:16:30,781 --> 00:16:31,907
[in English] What did she ever do?

315
00:16:31,991 --> 00:16:33,409
[in English] You let them be!

316
00:16:33,909 --> 00:16:35,869
Gavin, talk to your friend!

317
00:16:35,953 --> 00:16:38,455
Tell him not to act cute
or show off to Tonet.

318
00:16:39,456 --> 00:16:40,833
She's going through something.

319
00:16:40,916 --> 00:16:42,918
You heard that. Right, bro?

320
00:16:43,961 --> 00:16:46,547
[in English] I understand. A bit.

321
00:16:47,339 --> 00:16:48,799
[in English] Maybe we
should just be friends.

322
00:16:49,883 --> 00:16:51,385
[in English] No! You do not do that.

323
00:16:51,468 --> 00:16:52,678
That's called taking advantage.

324
00:16:52,761 --> 00:16:53,887
[in English] Not nice.

325
00:16:53,971 --> 00:16:55,139
[in English] Karla is right, bro.

326
00:16:55,222 --> 00:16:57,641
[in English] Be a gentleman.
Just keep your distance

327
00:16:57,725 --> 00:16:59,852
first while Tonet sorts herself out.

328
00:17:01,228 --> 00:17:02,104
[in English] Really?

329
00:17:02,187 --> 00:17:03,647
So, what?

330
00:17:03,731 --> 00:17:05,691
We won't see each other for the meantime?

331
00:17:05,774 --> 00:17:07,276
Oh? Why not?

332
00:17:07,359 --> 00:17:09,820
We can still play ball, right?
We'll make it up to you.

333
00:17:09,903 --> 00:17:10,779
[in English] Ball?

334
00:17:10,863 --> 00:17:12,614
[bright music playing]

335
00:17:12,698 --> 00:17:15,367
Wow! Basketball is all you're after?

336
00:17:15,868 --> 00:17:17,494
- Huh?
- [in English] Hotdog!

337
00:17:18,412 --> 00:17:20,164
- [in English] Hotdog?
- Eat first.

338
00:17:20,247 --> 00:17:21,582
Sis, do you have hotdog?

339
00:17:21,665 --> 00:17:22,541
- [Karla] Delicious.
- [vendor] No, just dumplings.

340
00:17:22,624 --> 00:17:24,376
- Just dumplings.
- Get some dumplings!

341
00:17:24,460 --> 00:17:25,961
- [Gaving] Bro.
- [indistinct]

342
00:17:26,045 --> 00:17:27,171
[JD] Game.

343
00:17:27,254 --> 00:17:28,338
Dumplings.

344
00:17:31,175 --> 00:17:32,885
[in English] "Big savings
on your cravings!"

345
00:17:32,968 --> 00:17:34,803
- [Ame] Ibyang…
- [Ibyang] Yummy.

346
00:17:34,887 --> 00:17:37,097
I changed the bed sheets already.
You can sleep now.

347
00:17:37,681 --> 00:17:38,766
[in English] Okay.

348
00:17:39,391 --> 00:17:43,854
- Uh, Ibyang, I'll just talk with Ame.
- [sniffles]

349
00:17:43,937 --> 00:17:45,689
We need to discuss something.

350
00:17:45,773 --> 00:17:47,733
- [in English] Okay.
- Mmm, all right.

351
00:17:47,816 --> 00:17:48,901
Yes, Ibyang.

352
00:17:48,984 --> 00:17:50,986
Go ahead. Go upstairs. Sleep now.

353
00:17:51,070 --> 00:17:52,279
We'll have a moment, Atoy and I. Go.

354
00:17:52,362 --> 00:17:53,697
- [Ibyang] Okay.
- [Atoy] Okay.

355
00:17:53,781 --> 00:17:55,866
[gentle music playing]

356
00:17:55,949 --> 00:17:57,159
What is it, Atoy?

357
00:17:57,242 --> 00:17:59,036
Do you know she can't read?

358
00:17:59,953 --> 00:18:01,080
[dramatic sting]

359
00:18:01,163 --> 00:18:02,164
What?

360
00:18:03,373 --> 00:18:04,249
Uh…

361
00:18:04,333 --> 00:18:05,584
That's impossible!

362
00:18:06,168 --> 00:18:07,211
Really?

363
00:18:07,294 --> 00:18:11,256
Yes! She can't read.

364
00:18:11,340 --> 00:18:12,883
[pensive music playing]

365
00:18:13,467 --> 00:18:14,927
[Atoy] I can't believe you didn't know.

366
00:18:15,427 --> 00:18:16,261
Oh, you.

367
00:18:16,345 --> 00:18:20,099
You prioritized teaching her street antics
instead of teaching her how to read, huh?

368
00:18:21,642 --> 00:18:23,519
Sorry.

369
00:18:24,019 --> 00:18:25,854
I really didn't know.

370
00:18:26,855 --> 00:18:30,692
Because she memorized prayers
at the orphanage,

371
00:18:31,193 --> 00:18:33,695
and she could sing English songs.

372
00:18:34,947 --> 00:18:37,157
What do you know about her parents?

373
00:18:38,408 --> 00:18:39,701
Nothing.

374
00:18:39,785 --> 00:18:43,038
When I met her, she was six years old
and already mischievous.

375
00:18:44,248 --> 00:18:47,000
But she said she was just a baby
when she was brought to the orphanage.

376
00:18:48,794 --> 00:18:50,712
[music concludes]

377
00:18:53,590 --> 00:18:54,716
Have some coffee first.

378
00:18:57,594 --> 00:18:58,804
Thank you, ‘Nang.

379
00:19:00,139 --> 00:19:01,723
Poor Ibyang.

380
00:19:01,807 --> 00:19:03,934
[gentle music playing]

381
00:19:05,894 --> 00:19:07,646
It's good I found out right away.

382
00:19:08,647 --> 00:19:11,859
So she won't grow up ignorant.

383
00:19:12,693 --> 00:19:14,278
What do you mean?

384
00:19:17,614 --> 00:19:18,991
I let Ibyang live here.

385
00:19:20,617 --> 00:19:22,286
I had no choice.

386
00:19:22,828 --> 00:19:25,664
Somehow, she's my responsibility now.

387
00:19:27,249 --> 00:19:28,375
You know?

388
00:19:28,458 --> 00:19:30,669
Like picking up a stone

389
00:19:30,752 --> 00:19:32,087
and hitting my own head with it.

390
00:19:34,256 --> 00:19:35,132
Like Dad.

391
00:19:37,676 --> 00:19:39,678
Like Dad with Emerson.

392
00:19:51,815 --> 00:19:52,774
[Atoy] Dad!

393
00:19:53,358 --> 00:19:54,818
Have you heard the rumor?

394
00:19:55,694 --> 00:19:58,989
That Emerson… He has no shame at all.

395
00:19:59,072 --> 00:20:02,409
He's setting up a tailoring shop,
and near you too!

396
00:20:02,993 --> 00:20:03,952
Oh, yes.

397
00:20:04,828 --> 00:20:07,206
At Miss Espi's house.

398
00:20:07,706 --> 00:20:08,707
[Atoy scoffs] The nerve!

399
00:20:08,790 --> 00:20:11,877
He didn't even wait
for Miss Espi to migrate.

400
00:20:11,960 --> 00:20:15,964
Imagine, he'll rent that place,
turn it into his shop!

401
00:20:17,799 --> 00:20:21,178
You know, I'm happy for Emerson.

402
00:20:21,970 --> 00:20:25,474
Because when I first met him,
he could hardly speak Tagalog.

403
00:20:26,099 --> 00:20:30,103
He was shy and didn't know how to sew
as his life depended on it.

404
00:20:31,563 --> 00:20:32,564
And now…

405
00:20:33,690 --> 00:20:38,445
he has the courage to open
his own tailoring shop.

406
00:20:39,238 --> 00:20:40,822
Yes, exactly.

407
00:20:40,906 --> 00:20:44,076
So, are you okay with Emerson
being your business rival, Dad?

408
00:20:44,701 --> 00:20:45,577
[chuckles softly]

409
00:20:46,870 --> 00:20:48,830
You know, when I met Emerson,

410
00:20:49,331 --> 00:20:55,712
he was like a rough, dusty stone.

411
00:20:57,923 --> 00:21:00,342
But now, a bit smoother

412
00:21:00,842 --> 00:21:03,720
and shining because of his own skill.

413
00:21:03,804 --> 00:21:05,931
[gentle music playing]

414
00:21:06,014 --> 00:21:07,099
[in English] Wow.

415
00:21:07,766 --> 00:21:09,393
[scoffs] Amazing.

416
00:21:09,977 --> 00:21:12,688
Emerson is lucky to have you, Dad.

417
00:21:12,771 --> 00:21:15,691
When you pick up or come across something,

418
00:21:16,984 --> 00:21:19,736
whether a person, an animal,

419
00:21:20,237 --> 00:21:21,697
or any object,

420
00:21:22,572 --> 00:21:26,785
leave it better
than when you first found it.

421
00:21:28,036 --> 00:21:29,496
You know, son…

422
00:21:30,289 --> 00:21:32,332
I won't be in this world for long.

423
00:21:32,833 --> 00:21:39,214
At least I'll leave knowing
the rough stone

424
00:21:39,715 --> 00:21:42,009
I struck against my head has improved.

425
00:21:42,634 --> 00:21:44,344
[sighs]

426
00:21:49,599 --> 00:21:53,020
[music continues]

427
00:22:02,321 --> 00:22:05,615
After Queenie, I'll focus on Ibyang…

428
00:22:06,658 --> 00:22:08,160
So she'll be all right.

429
00:22:08,243 --> 00:22:09,578
[somber music playing]

430
00:22:09,661 --> 00:22:12,205
I don't want her parents
to say anything against me.

431
00:22:13,665 --> 00:22:16,376
You'll look for Ibyang's parents?

432
00:22:17,878 --> 00:22:19,046
Why not?

433
00:22:20,589 --> 00:22:25,093
So, when I return her to them,

434
00:22:25,177 --> 00:22:27,721
she'll know that somehow,
she became better because of me.

435
00:22:28,764 --> 00:22:33,435
[sentimental music playing]

436
00:22:39,608 --> 00:22:42,319
- [Audrey, in English] Hi, Dad!
- [in English] Mmm! Morning!

437
00:22:45,072 --> 00:22:48,700
So, where did you and Gavin go yesterday?

438
00:22:48,784 --> 00:22:51,620
Ah, just around Baclaran.

439
00:22:52,120 --> 00:22:53,997
[in English] Oh, that's new.

440
00:22:55,123 --> 00:22:58,877
I didn't know you liked
going to places like that.

441
00:22:58,960 --> 00:23:00,754
Was it Baclaran church?

442
00:23:00,837 --> 00:23:02,756
Ah, another church, actually.

443
00:23:02,839 --> 00:23:03,799
Um…

444
00:23:04,299 --> 00:23:06,301
We went there for something.

445
00:23:07,219 --> 00:23:10,305
We visited the miraculous image
of St. Anthony,

446
00:23:10,806 --> 00:23:13,225
the patron saint of lost things.

447
00:23:14,101 --> 00:23:18,313
I prayed that he would help me find
the man I met on the island.

448
00:23:19,606 --> 00:23:21,316
[pensive music playing]

449
00:23:21,399 --> 00:23:22,943
[sighs] Darling…

450
00:23:24,820 --> 00:23:30,784
[in English] You know, some people
just pass by our lives.

451
00:23:31,284 --> 00:23:32,869
[in English] They don't intend to stay.

452
00:23:33,453 --> 00:23:36,289
[in English] Sometimes they don't
even want to be found.

453
00:23:37,457 --> 00:23:42,212
[in English] Yes, but they come
into our lives for a reason.

454
00:23:42,796 --> 00:23:44,589
Darling, I'm worried about you.

455
00:23:44,673 --> 00:23:47,342
You might get too obsessed with that man,

456
00:23:47,884 --> 00:23:50,303
when he's not even looking for you.

457
00:23:52,013 --> 00:23:54,975
[in English] Ah, but anyway, I have to go.

458
00:23:55,892 --> 00:23:58,562
I'll head to our shipping office.

459
00:23:58,645 --> 00:23:59,521
[in English] All right?

460
00:24:00,188 --> 00:24:02,440
- [in English] Okay. Bye, Dad.
- [in English] All right. Bye-bye.

461
00:24:03,483 --> 00:24:06,111
[music swells]

462
00:24:10,490 --> 00:24:16,204
[suspicious music playing]

463
00:24:36,224 --> 00:24:37,434
Audrey?

464
00:24:44,691 --> 00:24:45,525
Audrey?

465
00:24:47,485 --> 00:24:49,905
[in English] I… I am looking for my phone.

466
00:24:49,988 --> 00:24:51,531
[in English] Did I leave it somewhere?

467
00:24:51,615 --> 00:24:52,616
[Audrey] Uh…

468
00:24:52,699 --> 00:24:55,285
[tense music playing]

469
00:24:55,368 --> 00:24:57,037
[in English] Ah! Here it is, Dad.

470
00:24:57,120 --> 00:24:59,497
[in English] Oh, okay. Thank you.

471
00:25:01,166 --> 00:25:02,918
- [in English] Bye!
- [Dmitri in English] Bye!

472
00:25:10,800 --> 00:25:13,053
[line rings]

473
00:25:14,221 --> 00:25:16,640
[in English] Hello? Is this Mr. Mercado?

474
00:25:17,641 --> 00:25:19,517
[in English] Are you the contact
for The Master Cutter?

475
00:25:24,231 --> 00:25:27,442
[tense music playing]

476
00:25:31,863 --> 00:25:33,156
[Enzo] <i>Sorry, I forgot to mention earlier.</i>

477
00:25:33,240 --> 00:25:34,783
There's an event here now,
punk rock bands.

478
00:25:34,866 --> 00:25:36,618
More people will come,
and it'll get louder!

479
00:25:36,701 --> 00:25:38,703
Did she say which friend
she's meeting up with?

480
00:25:38,787 --> 00:25:40,121
Was it Raki?

481
00:25:40,205 --> 00:25:41,039
[Tonet] You're a red flag!

482
00:25:41,122 --> 00:25:43,500
Just because you're a rockstar
doesn't mean you get everything!

483
00:25:43,583 --> 00:25:45,752
That's what I like.
Those who play hard to get.

484
00:25:45,835 --> 00:25:48,672
That's why Tonet is getting
close to the kidnappers,

485
00:25:48,755 --> 00:25:50,048
because you push her away!

486
00:25:50,131 --> 00:25:51,466
Kidnappers?

487
00:25:51,549 --> 00:25:54,302
Not sure yet, but he's with Tonet now.

488
00:25:54,386 --> 00:25:55,428
Here, they have a gig.

489
00:25:55,512 --> 00:25:57,180
[Karla] <i>Punk Man event. Later tonight.</i>

490
00:25:57,264 --> 00:25:58,515
♪ <i>Oh, Mr. Tailor</i> ♪

491
00:25:58,598 --> 00:25:59,933
♪ <i>Holding the scissors</i> ♪

492
00:26:00,016 --> 00:26:00,850
UP NEXT

493
00:26:00,934 --> 00:26:04,813
♪ <i>One cut, and it's settled</i> ♪

494
00:26:04,896 --> 00:26:07,399
Subtitle translation by: Rachel C. Arias
